1
00:00:11,733 --> 00:00:14,333
Did you report Dr. Miranda
to the police?

2
00:00:14,400 --> 00:00:16,933
I was just trying
to teach Mookie a lesson.

3
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:19,300
Bringing her to a doctor
with a revoked license

4
00:00:19,367 --> 00:00:21,167
and willing to cut her legs off?

5
00:00:21,233 --> 00:00:23,433
If you like, we can adopt.

6
00:00:23,500 --> 00:00:24,767
So, at least,

7
00:00:24,833 --> 00:00:28,333
you don't have to spend time
with a kid unrelated to you.

8
00:00:28,400 --> 00:00:32,333
You're lucky I decided to delay
your leg amputation.

9
00:00:32,400 --> 00:00:34,067
What are you thinking?

10
00:00:34,167 --> 00:00:35,533
Why do you seem so happy?

11
00:00:35,600 --> 00:00:38,400
I'm thinking about the time
you read me a storybook.

12
00:00:38,467 --> 00:00:39,767
Give that to me!

13
00:00:39,833 --> 00:00:42,000
- Hurry up! People are coming!
- She is my daughter's employer.

14
00:00:42,067 --> 00:00:43,933
Her name is Olive Caparas.

15
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:45,800
So, this is just a minor injury.

16
00:00:45,867 --> 00:00:47,867
Which means I can be discharged.

17
00:00:47,933 --> 00:00:50,900
You might get delayed reactions
from your head trauma.

18
00:00:50,967 --> 00:00:52,133
I need to go home.

19
00:01:30,700 --> 00:01:32,400
How did you get in here, Emma?

20
00:01:33,933 --> 00:01:35,100
I told you...

21
00:01:36,133 --> 00:01:38,533
Give me a little consideration,
Emma.

22
00:01:38,600 --> 00:01:41,767
If you're not afraid
to get caught by Ma'am Olive,

23
00:01:41,867 --> 00:01:43,267
please think about me!

24
00:01:44,300 --> 00:01:46,867
I'll be going home later
for Aryen's graduation.

25
00:01:46,933 --> 00:01:48,767
What if you get caught?

26
00:01:48,833 --> 00:01:50,600
I'll be in trouble, too!

27
00:01:50,667 --> 00:01:52,867
She won't allow me to go home!

28
00:01:52,933 --> 00:01:54,000
Come on!

29
00:02:02,500 --> 00:02:03,767
Flor...

30
00:02:05,433 --> 00:02:06,767
look at this.

31
00:02:18,600 --> 00:02:19,433
Mookie?

32
00:02:20,700 --> 00:02:21,933
You can walk again?

33
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:23,233
You can walk again!

34
00:02:24,667 --> 00:02:25,500
How?
When?

35
00:02:26,467 --> 00:02:27,867
It's just baby steps,

36
00:02:27,933 --> 00:02:31,567
but I've just learned
to walk again.

37
00:02:32,333 --> 00:02:34,667
Thanks to Mommy...

38
00:02:37,100 --> 00:02:39,133
Thanks to Emma's help.

39
00:02:50,100 --> 00:02:52,267
Hello, Miss Caparas.

40
00:02:52,333 --> 00:02:54,967
Doc, what happened?

41
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:58,867
Okay, based on your CT scan,

42
00:02:58,933 --> 00:03:00,667
you have a minor edema
in your brain.

43
00:03:00,733 --> 00:03:02,233
That's why there is swelling.

44
00:03:03,367 --> 00:03:06,600
I highly recommend you to stay
for your own safety.

45
00:03:06,667 --> 00:03:10,867
Otherwise, sign the discharge
against medical advice form.

46
00:03:10,933 --> 00:03:13,500
That is if you're willing
to take the risk.

47
00:03:13,567 --> 00:03:14,700
But if I were you,

48
00:03:14,767 --> 00:03:17,167
I would get some rest,
Ms. Caparas.

49
00:03:17,233 --> 00:03:18,267
See you in a while.

50
00:03:39,833 --> 00:03:41,667
Flor, don't be mad.

51
00:03:43,500 --> 00:03:44,900
Please.

52
00:03:44,967 --> 00:03:46,000
Oh, you...

53
00:03:46,067 --> 00:03:49,133
I would have beaten you up
if Mookie wasn't here.

54
00:03:49,200 --> 00:03:50,933
Leave, and go home!

55
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:59,100
Flor, maybe Emma
can stay a little?

56
00:03:59,200 --> 00:04:01,733
Mommy won't be here until later.

57
00:04:01,800 --> 00:04:02,800
Come on, Mookie.

58
00:04:02,867 --> 00:04:04,333
Please, Flor.

59
00:04:08,633 --> 00:04:11,000
Fine. But only for an hour.

60
00:04:11,067 --> 00:04:12,200
Thank you, Flor.

61
00:04:15,367 --> 00:04:16,733
Thank you, Flor.

62
00:04:16,800 --> 00:04:17,333
Okay.

63
00:04:17,400 --> 00:04:18,733
Clean this up.

64
00:04:18,800 --> 00:04:20,033
Yes. I'll take care of it.

65
00:04:29,800 --> 00:04:33,767
Okay, I'm on my way back there.
Wait for me.

66
00:04:33,833 --> 00:04:35,133
You don't have to.

67
00:04:35,200 --> 00:04:37,233
I've found a replacement.

68
00:04:37,300 --> 00:04:38,733
Why did you go with her?

69
00:04:38,800 --> 00:04:40,667
You know, I have no idea either.

70
00:04:40,733 --> 00:04:44,333
But I'll join you. Wait for me.

71
00:04:44,400 --> 00:04:45,700
I said no.

72
00:04:45,767 --> 00:04:48,433
We're already enjoying the game.
I've won 3,000 pesos already.

73
00:04:48,500 --> 00:04:50,167
The players are so dumb.

74
00:04:50,233 --> 00:04:51,167
3,000 pesos?

75
00:04:52,067 --> 00:04:56,500
Son of a gun!

76
00:04:56,567 --> 00:04:59,700
Fine! You're lucky, and I'm not!

77
00:04:59,767 --> 00:05:00,700
Goodbye!

78
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:02,100
Give me some of your winnings.

79
00:05:27,200 --> 00:05:30,233
Mookie, you have lots of dolls.

80
00:05:32,767 --> 00:05:33,800
Yes.

81
00:05:33,900 --> 00:05:36,033
Mommy gave them all.

82
00:05:38,533 --> 00:05:43,533
Is it true that your mom
doesn't want you to walk?

83
00:05:43,600 --> 00:05:44,867
Yes.

84
00:05:44,933 --> 00:05:48,100
She always discourages me
to walk.

85
00:05:48,167 --> 00:05:52,167
She said it was hopeless.

86
00:05:52,233 --> 00:05:55,900
But you saw it.
Right, Mommy Emma?

87
00:05:55,967 --> 00:05:57,367
Yes.

88
00:05:57,433 --> 00:05:58,833
You were able to walk earlier.

89
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:02,433
I'll just bring this down.

90
00:06:02,500 --> 00:06:03,433
Okay.

91
00:06:09,267 --> 00:06:10,867
Hello, Diary.

92
00:06:10,933 --> 00:06:14,200
Last night,
I was able to stand up.

93
00:06:14,267 --> 00:06:16,800
And earlier, I was able to walk!

94
00:06:16,867 --> 00:06:18,867
But only baby steps.

95
00:06:18,933 --> 00:06:20,533
I still can't do it.

96
00:06:20,600 --> 00:06:24,167
But with more practice,
I think I can do it.

97
00:06:26,333 --> 00:06:27,867
Mookie! Oh, no, Mookie!

98
00:06:27,933 --> 00:06:29,700
Your mom is calling.

99
00:06:29,767 --> 00:06:31,633
Answer it, hurry!
There, there!

100
00:06:31,700 --> 00:06:33,033
She must not see me. Wait.

101
00:06:33,100 --> 00:06:34,467
I'll hide in here.

102
00:06:35,467 --> 00:06:36,933
Go on. Answer it, hurry.

103
00:06:39,933 --> 00:06:41,100
Hi, Mommy.

104
00:06:43,867 --> 00:06:45,767
Oh? Mommy, what happened to you?

105
00:06:45,833 --> 00:06:48,133
Why is your head in a bandage?

106
00:06:48,200 --> 00:06:51,067
I'm in the hospital.
I had an accident.

107
00:06:52,100 --> 00:06:53,367
What happened?

108
00:06:53,433 --> 00:06:55,400
My tire broke.

109
00:06:55,467 --> 00:06:58,533
And I almost got victimized
by a riding-in-tandem.

110
00:06:58,600 --> 00:07:00,133
What?

111
00:07:00,200 --> 00:07:05,100
Mommy, do you want Flor and me
to go to the hospital?

112
00:07:05,167 --> 00:07:06,900
I'm fine, I'm fine.

113
00:07:06,967 --> 00:07:08,867
Stop worrying, okay?

114
00:07:08,933 --> 00:07:12,000
And no, you're not coming here.

115
00:07:12,067 --> 00:07:15,433
You might catch an illness.
Your immune system is weak.

116
00:07:16,500 --> 00:07:18,233
Okay, Mommy.

117
00:07:18,300 --> 00:07:19,767
But how are you?

118
00:07:20,833 --> 00:07:22,733
I have an injury on my foot.

119
00:07:22,800 --> 00:07:24,800
My head aches.

120
00:07:24,867 --> 00:07:27,600
I want to go home,
but I'm under observation.

121
00:07:28,633 --> 00:07:34,133
Mookie, don't you ever try
to get up and walk.

122
00:07:34,200 --> 00:07:35,667
That's bad for you.

123
00:07:36,867 --> 00:07:37,800
Okay.

124
00:07:43,967 --> 00:07:45,100
Who's that?

125
00:07:45,167 --> 00:07:46,700
Is that Emma by the door?

126
00:07:49,133 --> 00:07:51,233
What is Emma doing in your room?

127
00:07:56,667 --> 00:07:58,700
Mookie, answer me!

128
00:07:58,767 --> 00:08:00,367
Let me see the door!

129
00:08:00,433 --> 00:08:02,400
I want to see who's in there.

130
00:08:10,700 --> 00:08:13,133
Show me who's at the door!

131
00:08:16,167 --> 00:08:17,867
Ma'am, it's me. It's me.

132
00:08:22,267 --> 00:08:24,967
Emma doesn't have work today,
Ma'am.

133
00:08:25,033 --> 00:08:29,300
And I won't let her go
to Mookie's room.

134
00:08:31,300 --> 00:08:33,067
It must be my head injury.

135
00:08:35,567 --> 00:08:36,433
Anyway, Flor...

136
00:08:37,533 --> 00:08:40,933
take care of Mookie
while I'm in the hospital.

137
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:43,667
And leave the tablet to her,
too.

138
00:08:43,733 --> 00:08:48,333
Ma'am, can Ma'am Astrid
look after Mookie?

139
00:08:48,400 --> 00:08:49,633
She's in Cebu.

140
00:08:51,100 --> 00:08:51,700
Wait.

141
00:08:52,967 --> 00:08:55,067
Are you disobeying me?

142
00:08:55,167 --> 00:08:56,600
No, Ma'am.

143
00:08:57,633 --> 00:09:00,567
But I asked your permission.

144
00:09:00,633 --> 00:09:03,100
I'm going home
for my child's graduation.

145
00:09:03,167 --> 00:09:06,467
I don't care about your
daughter's graduation.

146
00:09:07,500 --> 00:09:10,367
Just take care of Mookie.

147
00:09:14,400 --> 00:09:15,200
Are you okay?

148
00:09:35,633 --> 00:09:37,567
Hello, Madam!

149
00:09:39,167 --> 00:09:40,533
You, again?

150
00:09:43,333 --> 00:09:44,400
It's so annoying.

151
00:09:44,467 --> 00:09:46,533
This is the only time
I asked for something.

152
00:09:46,600 --> 00:09:47,700
But I was denied of it.

153
00:09:47,767 --> 00:09:50,067
Flor, you can't miss it.

154
00:09:50,133 --> 00:09:52,433
You should be at your
daughter's graduation.

155
00:09:53,833 --> 00:09:56,300
What about Mookie?
Who will take care of her?

156
00:09:56,367 --> 00:09:58,033
I will.

157
00:09:58,100 --> 00:09:59,133
You can't.

158
00:09:59,200 --> 00:10:01,833
What if she tells her mom?
We'll be in trouble.

159
00:10:01,933 --> 00:10:03,500
She won't do that.

160
00:10:05,467 --> 00:10:08,833
Honestly,
we decided to send you home.

161
00:10:08,900 --> 00:10:12,233
So you can be
at Aryen's graduation.

162
00:10:12,300 --> 00:10:14,267
Thank you.

163
00:10:14,333 --> 00:10:15,367
Thank you so much.

164
00:10:16,467 --> 00:10:18,867
You're so kind to me. Thank you.

165
00:10:18,933 --> 00:10:20,900
But, okay.

166
00:10:20,967 --> 00:10:22,100
I promise,

167
00:10:22,167 --> 00:10:23,900
I'll go back as soon as
the graduation is finished.

168
00:10:23,967 --> 00:10:25,733
Just don't tell our employer,
okay?

169
00:10:25,800 --> 00:10:28,367
It's between the two of us.
Don't say anything.

170
00:10:28,433 --> 00:10:29,567
I'm excited.

171
00:10:29,633 --> 00:10:31,033
My daughter will be glad.

172
00:10:31,100 --> 00:10:32,200
Thank you.

173
00:10:33,633 --> 00:10:35,667
You're so grumpy.

174
00:10:35,767 --> 00:10:37,733
You haven't thanked me yet.

175
00:10:37,800 --> 00:10:39,333
Get the hell out.

176
00:10:40,367 --> 00:10:42,400
And why would I thank you?

177
00:10:42,467 --> 00:10:43,500
Oh, Madam...

178
00:10:45,000 --> 00:10:48,700
I was with you when you were
rushed to the hospital.

179
00:10:48,767 --> 00:10:51,633
I was at the place
of the accident.

180
00:10:52,267 --> 00:10:55,200
You're probably an accomplice
of the riding-in-tandem.

181
00:10:55,267 --> 00:10:55,833
What?

182
00:10:59,800 --> 00:11:01,367
Madam, you're so mean.

183
00:11:02,467 --> 00:11:06,400
You can investigate me.
You won't see any record.

184
00:11:06,467 --> 00:11:07,800
So, why were you there?

185
00:11:08,933 --> 00:11:13,300
You know, Madam, I was supposed
to take a side hustle.

186
00:11:13,367 --> 00:11:18,333
But I chose to bring you
here in the hospital.

187
00:11:19,133 --> 00:11:20,600
So, that's why you're here.

188
00:11:21,667 --> 00:11:24,967
To ask me to pay for your
supposed side hustle.

189
00:11:25,033 --> 00:11:25,833
Of course not.

190
00:11:27,867 --> 00:11:30,767
Hey, but since you mentioned it,
you're right.

191
00:11:32,100 --> 00:11:34,400
I didn't earn the money
I was supposed to earn.

192
00:11:35,167 --> 00:11:37,500
But it's okay
because I was able to help you.

193
00:11:37,567 --> 00:11:39,567
Look, you're alive.
You're doing well.

194
00:11:39,633 --> 00:11:41,033
You're still pretty.

195
00:11:41,100 --> 00:11:42,400
Can you smile a little?

196
00:11:43,500 --> 00:11:44,600
Oh.

197
00:11:46,800 --> 00:11:48,800
I brought chicken porridge
for you.

198
00:11:56,133 --> 00:11:57,100
It smells good, right?

199
00:11:58,467 --> 00:12:00,767
Do I look like I eat trash?

200
00:12:03,367 --> 00:12:05,667
You're so mean.

201
00:12:05,733 --> 00:12:06,433
Madam...

202
00:12:07,467 --> 00:12:10,300
I bought this in the
hospital's canteen.

203
00:12:10,367 --> 00:12:11,600
This is clean.

204
00:12:13,667 --> 00:12:18,167
But you know what, Madam?
Gosh, this costs 120 pesos.

205
00:12:18,267 --> 00:12:19,533
It's so expensive, right?

206
00:12:19,600 --> 00:12:22,433
That left me with only
80 pesos in my wallet.

207
00:12:24,567 --> 00:12:26,300
Gosh.

208
00:12:26,367 --> 00:12:29,200
Are you here to extort money
from me?

209
00:12:30,900 --> 00:12:32,967
I get the word money.

210
00:12:33,033 --> 00:12:36,233
But what does extort mean?

211
00:12:40,233 --> 00:12:42,500
A person who asks
someone for money.

212
00:12:42,567 --> 00:12:43,967
- Extortionist.
- What?

213
00:12:45,300 --> 00:12:46,600
Racketeer.

214
00:12:53,200 --> 00:12:54,133
You're funny.

215
00:13:02,600 --> 00:13:04,200
Wait. Where are you going?

216
00:13:04,267 --> 00:13:05,867
I texted you.

217
00:13:05,933 --> 00:13:09,767
I didn't receive anything.
My phone died.

218
00:13:09,833 --> 00:13:10,767
What did you text me?

219
00:13:11,000 --> 00:13:13,433
I'll stay the night at Mookie's.

220
00:13:13,500 --> 00:13:14,000
What?

221
00:13:15,200 --> 00:13:16,333
Wait. You can't.

222
00:13:17,167 --> 00:13:18,767
Why are you going
to sleep there?

223
00:13:19,867 --> 00:13:22,300
Mookie's mother had an accident.
She's in the hospital.

224
00:13:22,400 --> 00:13:24,633
Mookie needs me.
She's alone in the house.

225
00:13:24,700 --> 00:13:26,267
Unbelievable.

226
00:13:26,333 --> 00:13:28,133
Everything is about Mookie!

227
00:13:28,200 --> 00:13:29,633
You care about nothing
but Mookie!

228
00:13:29,700 --> 00:13:32,233
Can you stop obsessing
with that kid?

229
00:13:35,133 --> 00:13:38,233
Madam, I should've just
stolen your wallet

230
00:13:38,300 --> 00:13:41,500
if all I want from you is money.

231
00:13:41,567 --> 00:13:43,633
I even secured
all your belongings.

232
00:13:43,700 --> 00:13:45,800
I gave them to the doctor.

233
00:13:45,867 --> 00:13:46,833
If I ask you for money,

234
00:13:46,900 --> 00:13:48,900
it's only for this
chicken porridge.

235
00:13:48,967 --> 00:13:50,733
And money for transportation.

236
00:13:52,400 --> 00:13:54,000
So, I'm right.

237
00:13:56,900 --> 00:13:58,233
Where's my bag?

238
00:13:59,300 --> 00:14:00,933
Where did you put it, Madam?

239
00:14:04,767 --> 00:14:05,667
Maybe it's here.

240
00:14:08,033 --> 00:14:09,300
Bag.

241
00:14:10,367 --> 00:14:13,033
I found it quick. Is this it?

242
00:14:15,333 --> 00:14:16,067
It's so nice.

243
00:14:19,733 --> 00:14:20,567
Here.

244
00:14:27,800 --> 00:14:28,733
She might catch you!

245
00:14:28,833 --> 00:14:30,900
Mookie needs me.

246
00:14:30,967 --> 00:14:35,633
You know, Dan,
I helped her walk earlier.

247
00:14:35,700 --> 00:14:38,033
I felt so happy because
she was ecstatic!

248
00:14:39,733 --> 00:14:40,367
Emma...

249
00:14:42,033 --> 00:14:42,667
why?

250
00:14:43,867 --> 00:14:46,000
Don't I make you
feel happy anymore?

251
00:14:46,067 --> 00:14:49,300
Come on, Dan.
Of course, you make me happy.

252
00:14:49,367 --> 00:14:51,133
You're a good husband.

253
00:14:51,200 --> 00:14:54,800
But it feels different
to like...

254
00:14:54,867 --> 00:14:55,467
To feel like...
To what?

255
00:14:56,467 --> 00:14:57,700
To feel like you're a mother?

256
00:14:57,767 --> 00:14:59,500
Emma, there's nothing wrong
with that

257
00:14:59,567 --> 00:15:03,100
if Mookie is your daughter,
but she's not, right?

258
00:15:04,633 --> 00:15:06,800
This happened to us before
with Baby Samantha.

259
00:15:06,867 --> 00:15:09,867
That's why I'm suggesting
to adopt a child.

260
00:15:09,933 --> 00:15:14,167
So that you're going to love
and care for our own child!

261
00:15:18,400 --> 00:15:19,067
Madam...

262
00:15:20,100 --> 00:15:22,000
I have no change.

263
00:15:22,833 --> 00:15:24,467
Isn't that what you want?

264
00:15:25,467 --> 00:15:27,100
Just get the hell out.

265
00:15:28,800 --> 00:15:29,767
Right away?

266
00:15:31,767 --> 00:15:32,400
Madam.

267
00:15:34,667 --> 00:15:36,033
You're alone.

268
00:15:37,633 --> 00:15:39,033
You'll get bored.

269
00:15:40,233 --> 00:15:41,600
You have no one with you.

270
00:15:43,967 --> 00:15:45,500
Do you want to play cards?

271
00:15:46,733 --> 00:15:48,433
So you can kill time.

272
00:15:51,033 --> 00:15:52,067
I'll teach you, okay?

273
00:15:54,833 --> 00:15:56,267
You really are so pretty.

274
00:15:56,333 --> 00:15:58,133
Gosh.

275
00:15:58,200 --> 00:16:00,567
You'll be prettier if you smile.

276
00:16:02,500 --> 00:16:03,767
Wait.

277
00:16:09,300 --> 00:16:11,067
This is easy, Madam.

278
00:16:24,300 --> 00:16:27,733
We don't have to adopt, Danilo.

279
00:16:27,800 --> 00:16:31,867
I'm happy that I can make Mookie
feel my care as a mother

280
00:16:31,933 --> 00:16:33,967
that she doesn't feel
from her mom.

281
00:16:34,033 --> 00:16:35,467
I hope you understand.

282
00:16:35,533 --> 00:16:37,000
I don't understand!

283
00:16:38,600 --> 00:16:41,667
Because Mookie
isn't your daughter!

284
00:16:41,767 --> 00:16:44,300
You know, Emma,
you're at a disadvantage here!

285
00:16:44,367 --> 00:16:47,133
Because you will never be
Mookie's mother!

286
00:16:48,367 --> 00:16:50,900
You'll suffer in the end!

287
00:16:50,967 --> 00:16:52,967
I'm just worried about you!

288
00:16:54,000 --> 00:16:56,500
I don't worry about things
that haven't happened yet.

289
00:16:56,567 --> 00:17:00,433
What matters is the present!
Mookie needs me!

290
00:17:00,500 --> 00:17:01,367
Emma! Emma!

291
00:17:01,433 --> 00:17:02,533
Emma!

292
00:17:02,600 --> 00:17:04,333
Hey, Emma, let's talk this out.

293
00:17:04,400 --> 00:17:06,667
Let go of me! Mookie needs me!

294
00:17:06,733 --> 00:17:07,300
- What's wrong with you?
- Emma!
Dan!

295
00:17:24,500 --> 00:17:26,333
What happened to our den?

296
00:17:27,633 --> 00:17:28,533
I mean house.

297
00:17:30,067 --> 00:17:31,700
Did it break down already?

298
00:17:31,767 --> 00:17:34,600
No, Mother.
Emma and I had an argument.

299
00:17:35,567 --> 00:17:36,700
What?

300
00:17:39,633 --> 00:17:41,433
Did you hurt my daughter?

301
00:17:41,500 --> 00:17:43,600
- You dumbass!
- Ouch! Ouch!

302
00:17:43,667 --> 00:17:44,567
- How dare you!
- Ouch!

303
00:17:44,633 --> 00:17:46,867
You have no right
to hurt my child!

304
00:17:46,933 --> 00:17:48,100
- Darn you!
- Ouch, Mother!

305
00:17:48,200 --> 00:17:50,167
Return her to me
if you no longer want her!

306
00:17:50,233 --> 00:17:52,400
- Mom! Mom!
- You dumbass!

307
00:17:52,467 --> 00:17:53,900
I didn't hurt your daughter.

308
00:17:55,033 --> 00:17:56,633
This is where I took
my anger out!

309
00:17:56,700 --> 00:17:58,267
On this door.

310
00:17:58,333 --> 00:17:59,367
Are you sure?

311
00:17:59,433 --> 00:18:00,467
I am!

312
00:18:02,533 --> 00:18:07,933
If you do that,
I'll be playing cards in prison.

313
00:18:08,000 --> 00:18:10,400
Is that so?
Are you going to kill me?

314
00:18:10,467 --> 00:18:11,933
Of course! You know me!

315
00:18:14,367 --> 00:18:17,633
I love Emma even though
we're like cats and dogs.

316
00:18:18,900 --> 00:18:22,200
Sorry that you and your husband
had a misunderstanding

317
00:18:22,300 --> 00:18:23,867
because of me.

318
00:18:23,933 --> 00:18:26,000
It's not your fault.

319
00:18:26,067 --> 00:18:27,367
He's just worried for me.

320
00:18:27,433 --> 00:18:31,533
He said I've become
too close to you.

321
00:18:31,600 --> 00:18:35,967
What if we separate?
I'll be hurt too much.

322
00:18:36,033 --> 00:18:38,633
We're not going to separate,
Mom.

323
00:18:38,700 --> 00:18:39,900
Right?

324
00:18:39,967 --> 00:18:42,367
That's what I told him, too.

325
00:18:42,433 --> 00:18:45,367
But the same thing
happened once.

326
00:18:45,433 --> 00:18:47,767
I took care of a child.

327
00:18:47,833 --> 00:18:52,500
And I had a difficult time when
her mother took her from me.

328
00:18:53,533 --> 00:18:55,100
What did you two fight about?

329
00:18:56,333 --> 00:18:59,267
Mookie. Her employer's daughter.

330
00:18:59,333 --> 00:19:00,300
Why?

331
00:19:00,367 --> 00:19:02,500
She went there
to take care of the kid.

332
00:19:05,933 --> 00:19:07,000
Hey!

333
00:19:07,067 --> 00:19:08,700
That'll be an extra income.

334
00:19:08,767 --> 00:19:10,400
Yes, it's better
if she'll earn from it.

335
00:19:10,467 --> 00:19:12,000
But she won't.

336
00:19:12,067 --> 00:19:14,633
Because she volunteered
to do it.

337
00:19:14,700 --> 00:19:18,733
Her employer doesn't even
let her get near Mookie.

338
00:19:18,800 --> 00:19:23,133
Do you mean Emma's taking care
of her secretly?

339
00:19:23,200 --> 00:19:26,067
Yes, Mother.
That's the reason I'm annoyed.

340
00:19:27,233 --> 00:19:29,533
I understand Mr. Danilo.

341
00:19:31,033 --> 00:19:34,633
I'm sure he just loves you
so much.

342
00:19:34,700 --> 00:19:37,433
If Baby Kayla is here,

343
00:19:37,500 --> 00:19:40,733
Mr. Danilo probably
loves her so much, too.

344
00:19:48,600 --> 00:19:50,433
I'm sorry, Mom.

345
00:19:50,500 --> 00:19:52,767
I reminded you of her again.

346
00:19:55,033 --> 00:19:56,500
It's okay, Dear.

347
00:19:56,567 --> 00:19:58,100
It's true.

348
00:19:58,167 --> 00:19:59,300
You know,

349
00:19:59,367 --> 00:20:05,167
Danilo would've spoiled
Baby Kayla if she was here.

350
00:20:05,267 --> 00:20:10,200
But he didn't get to be
a father for too long.

351
00:20:10,267 --> 00:20:14,000
But if given a chance,
he'll be a good father.

352
00:20:15,667 --> 00:20:18,133
Baby Kayla would be lucky.

353
00:20:20,400 --> 00:20:24,600
She would've experienced
my life-long dream.

354
00:20:24,667 --> 00:20:26,733
To have a father.

355
00:20:31,433 --> 00:20:33,033
Let's eat, Mom.

356
00:20:33,100 --> 00:20:36,967
Go on and eat.
So you can take your medicine.

357
00:20:37,067 --> 00:20:37,733
Okay.
I'll get it?

358
00:20:39,767 --> 00:20:40,567
It's so good.

359
00:20:48,800 --> 00:20:49,467
Dear...

360
00:20:50,733 --> 00:20:53,267
do you take
all these medicines?

361
00:20:53,333 --> 00:20:54,633
You even have an injection.

362
00:20:58,100 --> 00:20:59,067
Yes, Mom.

363
00:21:01,600 --> 00:21:05,100
This is my steroids.

364
00:21:05,167 --> 00:21:09,767
And this is antispasmodic.

365
00:21:11,667 --> 00:21:16,100
There's another one that
my mom injects in my leg.

366
00:21:17,900 --> 00:21:20,033
What really is your illness?

367
00:21:20,100 --> 00:21:22,800
Mom said I have
an auto-immune disease.

368
00:21:22,867 --> 00:21:25,033
And leukemia.

369
00:21:25,100 --> 00:21:28,700
And I also have a spinal injury.

370
00:21:28,767 --> 00:21:29,967
With all your illnesses,

371
00:21:30,033 --> 00:21:33,033
why is your mom not bringing you
to another doctor?

372
00:21:33,100 --> 00:21:34,700
I don't know either.

373
00:21:35,733 --> 00:21:38,867
You're too young
to experience this.

374
00:21:38,933 --> 00:21:41,400
If only all your illnesses
can be transferred to me.

375
00:21:41,500 --> 00:21:44,167
So you won't suffer anymore.

376
00:21:44,233 --> 00:21:48,367
Mom, are you trying
to make me cry?

377
00:21:48,433 --> 00:21:49,500
Sorry.

378
00:21:49,567 --> 00:21:51,633
Let's just think
of happy thoughts.

379
00:23:00,233 --> 00:23:02,133
Is that your favorite hobby,
Dear?

380
00:23:03,400 --> 00:23:04,600
Yes, Mom.

381
00:23:04,667 --> 00:23:13,133
I love to watch and observe
birds, butterflies, and people.

382
00:23:19,733 --> 00:23:21,967
Dear, wait.

383
00:23:22,067 --> 00:23:23,967
I'll just check
on what I'm cooking.

384
00:23:24,033 --> 00:23:25,333
Okay, Mommy Emma.

385
00:24:42,867 --> 00:24:44,033
Mookie?

386
00:24:49,333 --> 00:24:50,333
Mookie!

387
00:25:00,033 --> 00:25:02,667
Can you bring me to an arcade?

388
00:25:02,767 --> 00:25:04,567
What if your mom finds out?

389
00:25:04,633 --> 00:25:07,767
I will be
your eyes and ears here.

390
00:25:07,833 --> 00:25:11,100
I will tell you if your employer
is already going home.

391
00:25:11,167 --> 00:25:12,900
Because if Madam Beautiful
finds out

392
00:25:12,967 --> 00:25:15,033
what you're doing
to her daughter,

393
00:25:15,100 --> 00:25:17,000
you won't just get fired.

394
00:25:17,067 --> 00:25:19,433
She might send you to prison,
too.

395
00:25:19,500 --> 00:25:21,433
Sorry for everything
I said last night.

396
00:25:21,500 --> 00:25:22,433
Mommy Emma.

397
00:25:23,900 --> 00:25:25,767
Danilo, this is Mookie.

398
00:25:27,433 --> 00:25:29,433
Why are you frowning?

399
00:25:29,500 --> 00:25:31,800
I can't call Mookie.

400
00:25:31,867 --> 00:25:35,500
Why don't you call Emma?
She's taking care of Mookie.

401
00:25:37,733 --> 00:25:38,867
What did you say?
